column1: Top rowa: telomeric repeating unit sequence and its corresponding base position.
Left columnb: the location of mutated units in IT185 indicated by chromosome arm and the number of the unit.
Position 1 is the closest to subtelomeric region.
All the mutations are assigned to the corresponding position in the original (unmutated) unit.
Insertion is indicated by + nucleotide (e.g. +T at position 5 corresponds to adding T after the fifth nucleotide of the unit).
Deletion is indicated by - nucleotide (e.g. -G at position 2 corresponds to missing G at the second nucleotide of the unit).
Base substitution is indicated by nucleotide to nucleotide  (e.g. G to T at position 5 corresponds to replacing G to T at the fifth nucleotide of the unit).
